WEBVTT

00:00.810 --> 00:12.408
[somber strings and guitar music playing]

00:31.920 --> 00:38.100
[sporadic laughter]

00:39.100 --> 00:41.520
Wait, can you say that again?
I can’t hear you.

00:42.320 --> 00:44.400
And have you heard from him,
any better?

00:44.800 --> 00:47.700
Ok… yeah.
Don’t worry.

00:48.880 --> 00:50.860
Yeah, I’ll talk to you tomorrow.
Love you.

00:50.860 --> 00:51.660
Sorry!

00:53.020 --> 00:53.820
Pardon?

00:53.820 --> 00:53.824
Pardon?
Sorry for being loud whilst
you were on the phone.

00:53.824 --> 00:56.500
Sorry for being loud whilst
you were on the phone.

00:56.600 --> 00:57.860
Oh… it’s ok.

00:59.740 --> 01:01.020
See you inside!

01:01.490 --> 01:04.120
[rhythmic guitar continues playing]

01:06.100 --> 01:09.250
She walked in hand and continued
on the same street light.

01:09.440 --> 01:11.940
“I left my gloves”,
she finally confesses.

01:12.040 --> 01:13.760
“I’m not going back”, I said.

01:17.380 --> 01:19.200
Anybody else?

01:20.960 --> 01:23.760
This is my poem, it’s called...

01:23.980 --> 01:25.820
‘Rage in Minor B,'

01:26.360 --> 01:28.380
'my fight with the Undemented'.

01:29.730 --> 01:30.980
[background chatter]

01:31.620 --> 01:33.780
Sorry Nathan, I’ve gotta go.

01:33.820 --> 01:35.530
No, there’s still so much
drinking to be done-

01:35.530 --> 01:37.150
I drove so I can’t really
have any more.

01:37.320 --> 01:38.780
Thanks, it’s been great though.

01:40.380 --> 01:41.180
Actually-

01:42.280 --> 01:43.400
Where are you going?

01:43.520 --> 01:44.260
What?

01:44.500 --> 01:45.400
What direction
are you driving?

01:45.410 --> 01:46.620
Oh, erh... east.

01:46.640 --> 01:48.240
Yeah, me too. I’m–

01:48.260 --> 01:50.040
Do you mind if
I grab a lift?

01:50.080 --> 01:51.960
No that’s fine,
but I’m going now.

01:51.960 --> 01:52.880
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah,
me too.

01:52.880 --> 01:54.900
I’m just gonna
finish this drink.

01:55.180 --> 01:55.920
Do you mind, or…

01:56.460 --> 01:57.620
No, that’s fine, yeah.

02:05.200 --> 02:07.180
Do you want me
to plate yours?

02:07.700 --> 02:09.419
Plate,
you mean plaite?

02:09.900 --> 02:11.720
Plate, plait…

02:12.260 --> 02:13.070
Whatever.

02:13.120 --> 02:15.840
Probably not
the best moment.

02:17.140 --> 02:18.520
Pull over then!

02:18.520 --> 02:20.520
[rhythmic guitar playing continues]

02:27.120 --> 02:28.460
[wind rushing in tunnel]

02:37.670 --> 02:38.760
[music fades out]

02:38.980 --> 02:41.960
You know I don’t have to leave you here,
I can take you home.

02:42.380 --> 02:43.720
What’s your number?

02:44.080 --> 02:46.080
We can hang out again
if you want.

02:46.700 --> 02:48.040
Thanks for the lift.

02:48.040 --> 02:50.040
I’ll let you know
if I go out.

02:51.540 --> 02:52.190
Sure.

02:54.330 --> 02:54.800
Bye!

02:54.870 --> 02:55.110
Bye.

02:57.615 --> 02:58.908
[chuckles]

03:07.120 --> 03:13.290
[slow, somber music with humming vocals]

03:59.260 --> 04:01.130
[speaking French]
Donne-moi de l'eau.

04:09.470 --> 04:11.100
[speaking French]
Au revoir!

04:11.100 --> 04:12.730
[speaking French]
Au revoir, Charlie.

04:21.899 --> 04:23.490
[somber music fades out]

04:35.120 --> 04:37.790
[door screeching]

05:09.620 --> 05:11.490
[bottles clinking]

05:13.250 --> 05:15.750
[car door shuts]

05:27.550 --> 05:30.680
[muffled voice on radio]

05:31.180 --> 05:32.600
[door opens]

06:00.580 --> 06:02.170
[door shuts]

06:26.990 --> 06:29.450
[birds chirping]

07:07.980 --> 07:09.280
[speaking French]
Excusez-moi,

07:09.280 --> 07:11.320
[speaking French]
C'est une propriétée privée içi.

07:12.520 --> 07:13.700
[speaking French]
Tu comprends?

07:14.980 --> 07:16.080
