that, you know.

09:13.140 --> 09:13.870
Oh, sorry!

09:13.870 --> 09:15.870
[Mia laughing]

09:21.500 --> 09:22.040
Who’s home?

09:25.110 --> 09:25.820
It’s my home.

09:27.180 --> 09:28.470
No, who is home?

09:29.810 --> 09:31.000
Oh. Nobody.

09:42.350 --> 09:44.810
[glass clinking]

09:48.210 --> 09:49.650
What do you think?

09:53.970 --> 09:55.390
I have to see it all first.

10:02.140 --> 10:04.200
I’ll show you where
you can sleep.

10:08.830 --> 10:13.710
[footsteps]

10:28.560 --> 10:29.440
[door shuts]

10:39.150 --> 10:42.620
[birds chirping]

11:06.320 --> 11:06.800
Morning!

11:08.590 --> 11:09.120
Morning.

11:12.880 --> 11:13.360
Ready?

11:15.770 --> 11:16.980
[slow guitar playing]

11:17.070 --> 11:17.560
Really?

11:19.320 --> 11:20.560
Do you want to sit
on the back?

11:20.590 --> 11:20.890
Yeah.

11:37.790 --> 11:38.800
Someone’s heavy.

11:44.150 --> 11:45.410
I hate this bike.

11:47.110 --> 11:49.460
You’ve been on it
like three seconds.

11:49.470 --> 11:50.140
Ouch!

11:53.750 --> 11:54.470
Get off the bike.

11:56.590 --> 11:57.140
Please.

11:58.620 --> 11:59.820
I’m leaving
your jacket.

11:59.850 --> 12:00.120
No.

12:00.380 --> 12:00.960
I’m leaving it.

12:07.490 --> 12:10.000
[music becoming more intense]

12:29.140 --> 12:32.310
[church bells ringing]

12:38.070 --> 12:38.770
Oh shit!

12:53.490 --> 12:57.170
I’ll ask the bar if they
can hang on to it.

13:06.590 --> 13:09.140
[slow guitar and electronic music]

13:19.180 --> 13:20.900
What are you doing in Vaiges?

13:24.650 --> 13:25.680
You’re such a pisshead.

13:27.720 --> 13:30.030
I told you last night.

13:34.490 --> 13:36.380
If you can’t be bothered
to listen, then…

13:36.570 --> 13:39.140
