Yeah.

20:55.060 --> 20:56.690
My back, like, aches!

20:56.690 --> 20:57.770
Yeah?

20:57.770 --> 20:59.520
Heavy, the bass.

20:59.900 --> 21:01.190
I wouldn’t know.

21:07.740 --> 21:08.570
Looks good.

21:08.570 --> 21:09.200
Good.

21:15.790 --> 21:17.330
[door closes]

21:20.130 --> 21:22.210
Oh my, smells good.

21:22.380 --> 21:24.210
Mum, this is my
friend, Mia.

21:24.210 --> 21:25.720
Hi, Cynthia.

21:25.930 --> 21:26.800
Mia.

21:26.880 --> 21:28.340
Is Charlie coming?

21:28.470 --> 21:30.930
No, he thinks he might
have to go back,

21:30.930 --> 21:32.180
he says his dad’s worse.

21:32.180 --> 21:33.060
Oh dear.

21:34.020 --> 21:35.690
Mia–
It’s Mia, right?

21:35.730 --> 21:36.190
Yeah.

21:36.230 --> 21:37.520
Would you like a drink?

21:37.980 --> 21:41.190
Yeah, do you want me to
go out and get some wine, or…

21:41.190 --> 21:41.770
No.

21:43.070 --> 21:45.030
Courtesy of work.

21:46.450 --> 21:49.700
God I stink of grease
from that place.

21:49.700 --> 21:51.700
Ella. Ella.

21:54.540 --> 21:58.170
So he said “Yeah, I wouldn’t mind”,
I figured I’d give it a go.

21:58.460 --> 22:02.420
See if I could use some of
my old, old contacts.

22:02.460 --> 22:04.460
So now you’re
managing him?

22:04.670 --> 22:05.800
Yeah.

22:05.800 --> 22:07.010
Do you like him?

22:07.090 --> 22:08.260
What do I know.

22:08.380 --> 22:09.220
Could be fun.

22:09.220 --> 22:10.350
[quiet song on CD player]

22:10.350 --> 22:11.300
Yeah.

22:15.350 --> 22:15.730
Yeah.

22:18.770 --> 22:20.650
Mainly bar work at the moment.

22:20.650 --> 22:22.730
No Mia’s in a band
and they’re really good!

22:22.980 --> 22:26.030
Yeah well. You sold your opinion
on music when you said

22:26.900 --> 22:28.490
“what do I know”.

22:28.490 --> 22:32.740
Well Mia, when I make it
as a music manager,

22:32.740 --> 22:35.120
I’ll sign you to my label.

22:35.410 --> 22:36.450
Perfect.

22:40.540 --> 22:42.670
Only cause you are.

22:51.340 --> 22:54.560
[suspenseful electronic hum]

22:56.720 --> 22:58.310
Close the window.

23:00.060 --> 23:02.650
Do you find yourself
worrying about men, Mia?

23:04.110 --> 23:04.940
No.

23:04.940 --> 23:07.860
I think I should give up
worrying about them.

23:10.740 --> 23:16.080
Ella, you found Charlie and
everything you need.

23:18.700 --> 23:24.460
Security, money, family.
It’s all I want for you.

23:26.090 --> 23:28.170
It’s all I ever wanted.

23:28.510 --> 23:32.470
He’s–
Charlie, he’s just so…

23:33.720 --> 23:36.010
You know Mia, you
know what I mean.

23:36.010 --> 23:40.480
You should share the responsibility
to look after yourself with someone else.

23:40.480 --> 23:43.190
Which is what I
should have done.

23:43.310 --> 23:46.400
But Mia, you’re free.

23:46.400 --> 23:50.400
You can do what you want.
Ella, me, we can’t.

23:51.030 --> 23:53.660
You don’t have the consequences.

23:55.370 --> 24:01.250
You don’t have the weight of
consequences following you around.

24:01.250 --> 24:02.920
That’s freedom!

24:07.090 --> 24:10.380
Mum… go to bed.

24:20.220 --> 24:23.810
So now Charlie’s here I think my
mum thinks everything’s sorted.

24:25.610 --> 24:26.770
Why?

24:29.610 --> 24:31.780
His grandad left him a house.

24:34.610 --> 24:35.450
Where?

24:35.620 --> 24:36.700
France.

24:52.010 --> 24:54.090
I’m cooking for you tonight.

24:58.640 --> 24:59.760
[door unlocks]

24:59.760 --> 25:03.020
[slow cello music building throughout scene]

25:18.162 --> 25:20.540
[whispering]

26:01.990 --> 26:04.160
Have you thought about it?

26:05.080 --> 26:05.960
What?

26:08.290 --> 26:10.040
Which room?

26:10.460 --> 26:12.170
In my dream…

26:14.340 --> 26:15.630
I see you…

26:18.590 --> 26:21.470
Walking across the gravel at night.

26:26.270 --> 26:28.140
You look back at me.

26:33.150 --> 26:35.070
You start to undress.

26:46.160 --> 26:48.870
You walk off before
I can see anything.

26:56.210 --> 26:58.010
I never get to you in time.

27:05.010 --> 27:07.270
[footsteps disappear]

27:51.020 --> 27:51.890
Here.

28:01.700 --> 28:02.990
Here.

28:43.820 --> 28:44.950
Not yet.

28:50.540 --> 28:52.080
Do it, Mia.

28:56.130 --> 28:57.380
Do it, Mia.

29:11.770 --> 29:13.350
[cello music stops]

29:13.850 --> 29:15.480
Do it now.

29:22.570 --> 29:25.070
[voices on TV]

30:14.330 --> 30:15.960
Do you wanna hang out today?

30:16.410 --> 30:17.670
I gotta study today.

30:19.540 --> 30:20.790
Maybe later?

30:23.960 --> 30:25.420
Maybe.

